.@trianglestartup A8 (cont’d): That's what I've got right now, but if anybody has further questions, I'm more than happy to chat :) #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A8 (cont’d): You're building a network, so don't pass up opportunities to grow that network. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A8 (cont’d): 1) "Who else would you suggest I talk to?” and 2) “Would you mind making an introduction?” #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A8 (cont’d): Never ever ever end a meeting without asking these two questions... #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A8 (cont’d): But if you don’t ask, you don’t get. People can’t read your mind, so if you need something, ask! #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A8: Whenever you get a meeting, remember they’re doing you a favor. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A7 (cont'd): Networking is a big part of the @RocketBolt culture, so everything we do comes from that place. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A7: It's helped in every single way. Networking has gotten us customers, funding, mentorship, even office space. #TSWchat
.@DaveNealVC Don't make me blush during my Tweet chat, Dave! #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup @Gladwell A6 (cont'd): everyone at @HQRaleigh; Mark Easley; & many more. I'm sure I'm forgetting a ton of people. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup @Gladwell A6 (cont'd): @AdamMKlein, @AUEllieG, @mollydemarest and the @AmerUnderground team #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup @Gladwell A6: So many! @DaveNealVC, @ChrisHeivly, and @LizzyHazeltine at @TSF_VC; John Austin and @groundworklabs #TSWchat
.@georgeju @trianglestartup Love it. Very well said. #TSWchat
.@georgeju @trianglestartup Yeah. People will forever remember the way you make them feel. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A5 (cont'd): Having said that, the larger your team's network is, the better. I absolutely believe that. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A5 (cont'd): Your team needs complementary skills, not completely overlapping ones. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A5: I don't think everyone on the team needs to be a master networker for your company to be successful. #TSWchat
.@georgeju @trianglestartup Absolutely! Differences make for vibrant relationships, but hard to START there :) Find common ground. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A4 (cont'd): Be helpful, and you'll be helped when you need it. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A4 (cont'd): Pretty self-explanatory, but again: people help those they have a relationship with. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A4 (cont'd): ...than you can in two years by trying to get other people interested in you. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A4 (cont'd): You can make more friends in two months by becoming interested in other people... #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup I don’t know about a book, but here’s a Dale Carnegie quote that's always stuck with me: #TSWchat
Always looking for input @jkennedy93 :) Good to see you out and about in the Twitterverse! #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A3 (cont'd): Focus on what you can do for the other person rather than what you can get. That's a great start.  #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A3 (cont'd): Offer to help BEFORE you ask for help. That's how to not be a jerk about it :)  #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A3 (cont'd): Establish a relationship first. Ask about the other person... and actually listen to the answer. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A3 (cont’d): Focus on building the relationships 1st, 2nd, and 3rd. It's about honestly engaging with new people. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A3 (cont'd): Just have to be honest, patient, and humble with new relationships. Make people WANT to help you. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A3 (cont'd): It all starts with "Hello!" Starting new conversations can be tough, but people are willing to help. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A3: Lots to say about this. Settle in for a minute :)  #TSWchat
.@jkennedy93 Totally! The good news about networking is: if you do it right, not only is it useful, it's also fun and rewarding :) #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A2 (cont'd): Nobody does it alone. I've been helped every step of the way. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A2: Networking's vital because your personal and professional networks can help you reach your career goals. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A1 (cont'd): Anything that gets you talking to and meeting new people. No end to the formats that could take. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A1 (cont'd): That could mean attending events in person, or reaching out to people on social media. #TSWchat
.@trianglestartup A1: Networking is any interpersonal interaction that develops business contacts and builds relationships. #TSWchat
